{
  "stem": "21786.2",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 12.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "My grandfather, I remember, kept the high holidays, went to this little shul of this little-- one called-- can call it synagogue, it was too small for it, but still.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And I remember that he kept Passover.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Passover, he kept for, one point, for one ate matzohs.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And they brought-- a truck brought matzohs to the Jews in the local region.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And they were round, in parcels of about, I would say, 1 foot high.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And the whole village, all the farmers, all the peasants were waiting for the matzohs.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "For he brought the matzohs not only for himself, but every family had to get matzohs.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "It became some kind of a special feast towards a more special honor towards him.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "As I mentioned, I never met a speck of anti-Semitism in that village.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And that made it very difficult, for my grandfather was primarily a Czech.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "My grandmother was Czech.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "My mother was Czech.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "The Jewish, it was just incidental religion.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "There was absolutely no Jewish tradition in it.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "You know, and people start to talk about tradition.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "Tradition was gone at that point in time.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "The same way with father's side.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "They wanted to be German-- they wanted to be German more than being Jewish.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "So they became, I mean, what I then later find out was specific for the German Jews, [NON-ENGLISH], that-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] the kind of nationalism took over the religion.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "Obviously, it didn't pay.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "Now, we kept high holidays.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "We kept the Rosh Hashanah, we kept the Yom Kippur.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "And I remember that, at my uncle's, I had something like Hanukkah, occasionally-- not always.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "My grandfather would go so far that to comply with the village there was a-- a Christmas tree there.",
      "word_count": 19
    }
  ],
